<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911011-0037</DOCNO><DOCID>911011-0037.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Everex Systems Inc.:   Commerce Department Pact   Is Reached Over Exports</HL><DATE>10/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A4</SO><CO>   EVRX</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMPUTERS AND INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY (CPR)INTERNATIONAL TRADE NEWS (TRD)</IN><NS>TRADE ISSUES (TRD)</NS><GV>COMMERCE DEPARTMENT (COM)</GV><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)CHINA (CH)FAR EAST (FE)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Everex Systems Inc. said it reached a settlement with theCommerce Department concerning misclassification of certainexports. The Fremont, Calif., company said it and its FarEast unit received a penalty of $500,000, of which $225,000was suspended, for incorrectly classifying unfinishedproducts made in 1985 in China. The products were used in thecompany's products and exported from the U.S. Themanufacturing was prohibited under U.S. guidelines. Aspokesman said the violation was inadvertent, and that Everexvoluntarily informed the Commerce Department when it learnedof the misclassification in 1987. Everex makes personalcomputers and peripherals.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>